OL,5, A Japanese man who was on death row for
OL,6, nearly half a century has been granted 
OL,7, a retrial.                             
OL,9,FIwao Hakamada, now 87, is the world's  
OL,10,Flongest-serving death row inmate,      
OL,11,Faccording to Amnesty International.    
OL,13,FHe was sentenced to death in 1968 for  
OL,14,Fmurdering his boss, the man's wife and 
OL,15,Ftheir two children in 1966.            
OL,17,FThe former professional boxer confessed
OL,18,Fafter 20 days of interrogation during  
OL,19,Fwhich he said he was beaten. He later  
OL,20,Fretracted the confession in court.     
